	"contents": [
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "Custom Server"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "SSR Caching"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "By default, Next.js includes its own server with `next start`. If you have an existing backend, you can still use it with Next.js (this is not a custom server). A custom Next.js server allows you to start a server 100% programmatically in order to use custom server patterns. Most of the time, you will not need this - but it's available for complete customization."
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "> **Good to know**:\n>\n> * Before deciding to use a custom server, please keep in mind that it should only be used when the integrated router of Next.js can't meet your app requirements. A custom server will remove important performance optimizations, like **serverless functions** and &#x2A;*Automatic Static Optimization.**\n> * A custom server **cannot** be deployed on Vercel.\n> * Standalone output mode, does not trace custom server files and this mode outputs a separate minimal `server.js` file instead."
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "Take a look at the following example of a custom server:"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "> `server.js` doesn't go through babel or webpack. Make sure the syntax and sources this file requires are compatible with the current node version you are running."
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "To run the custom server you'll need to update the `scripts` in `package.json` like so:"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "The custom server uses the following import to connect the server with the Next.js application:"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "The above `next` import is a function that receives an object with the following options:"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "Option"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "Type"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "Description"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`conf`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`Object`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "The same object you would use in next.config.js. Defaults to `{}`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`customServer`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`Boolean`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "(*Optional*) Set to false when the server was created by Next.js"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`dev`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`Boolean`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "(*Optional*) Whether or not to launch Next.js in dev mode. Defaults to `false`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`dir`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`String`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "(*Optional*) Location of the Next.js project. Defaults to `'.'`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`quiet`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`Boolean`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "(*Optional*) Hide error messages containing server information. Defaults to `false`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`hostname`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`String`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "(*Optional*) The hostname the server is running behind"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`port`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`Number`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "(*Optional*) The port the server is running behind"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`httpServer`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "`node:http#Server`"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "(*Optional*) The HTTP Server that Next.js is running behind"
		},
		{
			"heading": void 0,
			"content": "The returned `app` can then be used to let Next.js handle requests as required."
		},
		{
			"heading": "disabling-file-system-routing",
			"content": "By default, `Next` will serve each file in the `pages` folder under a pathname matching the filename. If your project uses a custom server, this behavior may result in the same content being served from multiple paths, which can present problems with SEO and UX."
		},
		{
			"heading": "disabling-file-system-routing",
			"content": "To disable this behavior and prevent routing based on files in `pages`, open `next.config.js` and disable the `useFileSystemPublicRoutes` config:"
		},
		{
			"heading": "disabling-file-system-routing",
			"content": "> Note that `useFileSystemPublicRoutes` disables filename routes from SSR; client-side routing may still access those paths. When using this option, you should guard against navigation to routes you do not want programmatically."
		},
		{
			"heading": "disabling-file-system-routing",
			"content": "> You may also wish to configure the client-side router to disallow client-side redirects to filename routes; for that refer to `router.beforePopState`."
		}
	],
	"headings": [{
		"id": "disabling-file-system-routing",
		"content": "Disabling file-system routing"
	}]
